    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ANCHOR AWAY</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Robert Strauss</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Strauss, Robert</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey state Sen Diane Allen ends her return to television news anchor seat early after Democratic Senate leaders accuse her of going on air to advance her political career (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>State Senator Diane Allen (Republican, Burlington) ended her return to the television news anchor seat early after the Democratic Senate leadership accused her of going on the air to advance her political career. The Comcast channel CN8 had invited her to substitute during an anchor's two-week vacation. Senator Allen, who had a long career as a news anchor in Philadelphia before entering New Jersey politics five years ago, agreed to do so as long as she did not read any political news. After a week, Ms. Allen asked CN8 to pull out.</p>
        <p>Robert Strauss</p>
      </block>
